Today marks Mother’s Equal Pay Day, but it is not a celebration.

It’s a day to recognize how far we still have to go to close the gender wage gap in our country – especially for mothers whose pay lags 2 months behind the average woman. https://twitter.com/OversightDems/status/1400855091595427843 QT @OversightDems On average, working women are still paid only 82 cents for every dollar paid to a man, and mothers are even further behind.  

